{{Quote|You're sure the homing beacon is secure aboard their ship? I'm taking an awful risk, Vader. This had better work.|[[Grand Moff/Legends|Grand Moff]] [[Wilhuff Tarkin/Legends|Wilhuff Tarkin]]|<ref name="Episode 4">{{Film|IV}}</ref>}}
'''Homing droids''' were small, fifth-degree [[Droid/Legends|droids]] used as mobile tracking devices originally developed by spy agencies.

Homing droids were primarily vehicles used to plant [[Homing beacon/Legends|homing beacons]] on targets, though some models doubled as a homing device themselves. Commonly fitted with [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsorlifts]], homing droids were difficult to track, due to their ability to stay mobile and avoid detection. Some were fitted with defensive measures and self-destruct functions.

